# debug startup with: zsh -x -i -l -c true

# Load order:
# +----------------+-----------+-----------+------+
# |                |Interactive|Interactive|Script|
# |                |login      |non-login  |      |
# +----------------+-----------+-----------+------+
# |/etc/zshenv     |    A      |    A      |  A   |
# +----------------+-----------+-----------+------+
# |~/.zshenv       |    B      |    B      |  B   |
# +----------------+-----------+-----------+------+
# |/etc/zprofile   |    C      |           |      |
# +----------------+-----------+-----------+------+
# |~/.zprofile     |    D      |           |      |
# +----------------+-----------+-----------+------+
# |/etc/zshrc      |    E      |    C      |      |
# +----------------+-----------+-----------+------+
# |~/.zshrc        |    F      |    D      |      |
# +----------------+-----------+-----------+------+
# |/etc/zlogin     |    G      |           |      |
# +----------------+-----------+-----------+------+
# |~/.zlogin       |    H      |           |      |
# +----------------+-----------+-----------+------+
# |                |           |           |      |
# +----------------+-----------+-----------+------+
# |                |           |           |      |
# +----------------+-----------+-----------+------+
# |~/.zlogout      |    I      |           |      |
# +----------------+-----------+-----------+------+
# |/etc/zlogout    |    J      |           |      |
# +----------------+-----------+-----------+------+
# Source: https://medium.com/@rajsek/zsh-bash-startup-files-loading-order-bashrc-zshrc-etc-e30045652f2e):
